In a PEM fuel cell, hydrogen gas is ammited on one side of the membrane, and oxygen gas on the other side. Construction of a Hy/Ox fuel cell is relativly simple, the pain about it is water managment. The hydrogen side has to be kept moist or the membrane will begine to crack, and on the Oxygen side water must be removed or the cell will flood, rendering it usless untill drained. I will look for it among my printouts, I have one somewhere that tells you how to build a simple one, but with a little brainpower, could be used to make a fuel cell stack.<br>
